  "text": "The fix addresses a memory leak in the DFP cluster's cross-priority host map. The key files are:\n\n1. `cluster.cc`: Contains `addOrUpdateHost()` (lines 238-295) which currently does in-place address updates via `setNewAddresses()` instead of removing the old host and adding a new one. Also `onDnsHostAddOrUpdate()` (lines 297-308) which accumulates hosts_added before calling `updatePriorityState()`. Both need refactoring to properly emit hosts_added+hosts_removed events.\n\n2. `cluster.h`: Contains the `addOrUpdateHost()` declaration with the `hosts_added` out-parameter (lines 162-166) that needs to be simplified by removing that parameter.\n\n3. `cluster_test.cc`: The `BasicFlow` test (lines 237-273) needs updated expectations for the address-change path \u2014 the new implementation will emit a member update callback (hosts_added=1, hosts_removed=1) when the address changes, rather than silently updating in-place.\n\n4. `upstream_impl.cc`: The `updateCrossPriorityHostMap()` method (lines 830-851) operates on `host->address()` to key the map. Debug logging needs to be added here to trace cross-priority host map mutations (insertions/erasures).",
